.TH "drm_crtc_enable_color_mgmt" 9 "drm_crtc_enable_color_mgmt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_crtc_enable_color_mgmt \- enable color management properties
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_crtc_enable_color_mgmt
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ","
.BI "uint degamma_lut_size "  ","
.BI "bool has_ctm "  ","
.BI "uint gamma_lut_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
DRM CRTC
.IP "degamma_lut_size" 12
the size of the degamma lut (before CSC)
.IP "has_ctm" 12
whether to attach ctm_property for CSC matrix
.IP "gamma_lut_size" 12
the size of the gamma lut (after CSC)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function lets the driver enable the color correction
properties on a CRTC. This includes 3 degamma, csc and gamma
properties that userspace can set and 2 size properties to inform
the userspace of the lut sizes. Each of the properties are
optional. The gamma and degamma properties are only attached if
their size is not 0 and ctm_property is only attached if has_ctm is
true.
